integreat-cms

Views

This package contains simple unit tests for views. It just ensures that all views return the expected status code and does not check whether the response content is valid in any way.

  • Status Code
    • Test View Status Code_1
    • Test View Status Code_10

Test Public View Status Code

tests.cms.views.test_public_view_status_code.test_public_view_status_code(load_test_data: None, caplog: LogCaptureFixture, view_name: ViewNameStr, post_data: PostData) → None[source]

This test checks whether the given view return the correct status code for anonymous users

Parameters:

  • load_test_data (None) – The fixture providing the test data (see load_test_data())

  • caplog (LogCaptureFixture) – The caplog fixture

  • view_name (ViewNameStr) – The identifier of the view

  • post_data (PostData) – The post data for this view

Return type:

None

Test View Redirect

tests.cms.views.test_view_redirect.test_view_redirect(login_role_user: tuple[Client, str], caplog: LogCaptureFixture, view_name: ViewNameStr, kwargs: ViewKwargs, roles: Roles, target: RedirectTarget) → None[source]

This test checks whether the given view redirects to the given target url

Parameters:

  • login_role_user (tuple[Client, str]) – The fixture providing the http client and the current role (see login_role_user())

  • caplog (LogCaptureFixture) – The caplog fixture

  • view_name (ViewNameStr) – The identifier of the view

  • kwargs (ViewKwargs) – The keyword argument passed to the view

  • roles (Roles) – The list of roles which should experience the redirect

  • target (RedirectTarget) – The expected redirection target url

Return type:

None

Utils

tests.cms.views.utils.check_view_status_code(login_role_user: tuple[Client, str], caplog: LogCaptureFixture, view_name: ViewName, kwargs: ViewKwargs, post_data: PostData, roles: Roles) → None[source]

This test checks whether the given view return the correct status code for the current role

Parameters:

  • login_role_user (tuple[Client, str]) – The fixture providing the http client and the current role (see login_role_user())

  • caplog (LogCaptureFixture) – The caplog fixture

  • view_name (ViewName) – The identifier of the view

  • kwargs (ViewKwargs) – The keyword argument passed to the view

  • post_data (PostData) – The post data for this view

  • roles (Roles) – The list of roles which should be able to access this view

Return type:

None

This list contains the config for all views Each element is a tuple which consists of two elements: A list of view configs and the keyword arguments that are identical for all views in this list. Each view config item consists of the name of the view, the list of roles that are allowed to access that view and optionally post data that is sent with the request. The post data can either be a dict to send form data or a string to send JSON.
